{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857488321,"sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","part":{"id":"prt_d795acdd3001vULNFn0btZEts2","messageID":"msg_d795ac4cf001rXStxP6u3Htbfl","sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ce1fcc15467347abb58a62f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) 实现 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个子命令。`invoke` 用于向已部署的 agent 发送请求并获取响应，`status` 用于查询 agent 的运行状态和部署信息。\n10: \n11: ## 范围\n12: \n13: ### 包含\n14: \n15: 1. `invoke` Typer 命令实现\n16: 2. `status` Typer 命令实现\n17: 3. `InvokeRuntime` 类实现\n18: 4. `StatusRuntime` 类增强\n19: \n20: ### 不包含\n21: \n22: - `pack` / `build` / `publish` 命令的实现（由 AR-020 / AR-021 / AR-022 覆盖）\n23: - Go 二进制入口\n24: - CI/CD pipeline 变更\n25: \n26: ## 架构概要\n27: \n28: ```\n29: CLI Layer (Typer)\n30: ├── invoke() command → InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n31: └── status() command → StatusRuntime.status()\n32: \n33: Runtime Layer\n34: ├── InvokeRuntime — 发送 HTTP 请求到已部署的 agent endpoint\n35: └── StatusRuntime — 查询 K8s CR 或 Deployment 状态\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ## 上游依赖\n39: \n40: - **AR-022 (`publish` 命令)** — 依赖 publish 部署后的 agent endpoint 和 metadata\n41: \n42: ## 状态\n43: \n44: - [ ] 提案审查\n45: - [ ] 实现\n46: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 46 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\n为 AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) 实现 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个子命令。`invoke` 用于向已部署的 agent 发送请求并获取响应，`status` 用于查询 agent 的运行状态和部署信息。\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n1. `invoke` Typer 命令实现\n2. `status` Typer 命令实现\n3. `InvokeRuntime` 类实现\n4. `StatusRuntime` 类增强\n\n### 不包含","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857488306,"end":1775857488319}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857489641,"sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","part":{"id":"prt_d795ad22b001kbAgjZSQDQiQ4c","messageID":"msg_d795ac4cf001rXStxP6u3Htbfl","sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_965788d5290344d2853a38bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\n6: \n7: Both commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### 2.1 Data Flow\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n18: │   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\n19: │   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\n20: └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                          │\n22:           ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐\n23:           ▼                             ▼\n24: ┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n25: │    InvokeRuntime    │       │    StatusRuntime    │\n26: │                     │       │                     │\n27: │ .invoke()           │       │ .get_status()       │\n28: │  ├─ _validate_      │       │  ├─ load metadata   │\n29: │  │   prerequisites  │       │  ├─ _get_cr_k8s_    │\n30: │  ├─ _invoke_agent_  │       │  │   status()        │\n31: │  │   via_agentcube  │       │  └─ _get_k8s_       │\n32: │  └─ _direct_http_   │       │     status()        │\n33: │     invocation()    │       │                     │\n34: └────────┬────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n35:          │                             │\n36:          ▼                             ▼\n37: ┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n38: │  httpx / requests   │       │ AgentCubeProvider   │\n39: │  POST → endpoint    │       │ KubernetesProvider  │\n40: └─────────────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n41:                                        │\n42:                                        ▼\n43:                               ┌─────────────────────┐\n44:                               │   Rich Table Output │\n45:                               │   Field | Value     │\n46:                               └─────────────────────┘\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### 2.2 Package Layout (invoke/status-relevant modules)\n50: \n51: ```\n52: cmd/cli/\n53: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n54: ├── agentcube/\n55: │   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n56: │   ├── cli/\n57: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n58: │   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, invoke(), status(), _handle_error\n59: │   ├── models/\n60: │   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n61: │   ├── runtime/\n62: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n63: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          — InvokeRuntime class (NEW)\n64: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          — StatusRuntime class (NEW)\n65: │   └── services/\n66: │       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n67: │       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n68: │       ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService\n69: │       ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider (add get_agent_status)\n70: │       └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider (get_agent_runtime exists)\n71: └── tests/\n72:     ├── cli/\n73:     │   ├── test_invoke_command.py     — CLI invoke command tests (NEW)\n74:     │   └── test_status_command.py     — CLI status command tests (NEW)\n75:     └── runtime/\n76:         ├── test_invoke_runtime.py     — InvokeRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n77:         └── test_status_runtime.py     — StatusRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### 2.3 Dependencies\n81: \n82: | Module | Purpose |\n83: |--------|---------|\n84: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n85: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n86: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n87: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invoke requests |\n88: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output, tables |\n89: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional, for status providers) |\n90: \n91: No new dependencies are introduced — all are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Component Design\n96: \n97: ### 3.1 InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: class InvokeRuntime:\n101:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n102:     def invoke(\n103:         self,\n104:         workspace_path: Path,\n105:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n106:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n107:     ) -> Any: ...\n108:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n109:         self, workspace_path: Path\n110:     ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]: ...\n111:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n112:         self,\n113:         agent_id: str,\n114:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n115:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n116:         endpoint: str,\n117:         workspace_path: Path,\n118:     ) -> Any: ...\n119:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n120:         self,\n121:         endpoint: str,\n122:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n123:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n124:         workspace_path: Path,\n125:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n126: ```\n127: \n128: #### 3.1.1 `invoke()` — Main orchestration\n129: \n130: ```python\n131: def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n132:     # 1. Validate prerequisites — returns (metadata, agent_id, endpoint)\n133:     metadata, agent_id, endpoint = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n134: \n135:     # 2. Route by provider\n136:     if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n137:         return asyncio.run(\n138:             self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n139:         )\n140:     else:\n141:         return asyncio.run(\n142:             self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n143:         )\n144: ```\n145: \n146: #### 3.1.2 `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n147: \n148: Loads metadata and validates that the agent has been published:\n149: \n150: ```python\n151: def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n152:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n153:     metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n154: \n155:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n156:         raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n157:     if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n158:         raise ValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n159: \n160:     return metadata, metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint\n161: ```\n162: \n163: #### 3.1.3 `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` — AgentRuntime CR invocation\n164: \n165: Key behaviors:\n166: - **URL rewriting**: If `metadata.k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to:\n167:   ```\n168:   {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n169:   ```\n170:   where `base` is extracted from the original endpoint, `namespace` and `agent_name` come from `metadata.k8s_deployment`.\n171: - **Session header**: If `metadata.session_id` exists, add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header.\n172: - **HTTP POST**: Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` to POST JSON payload.\n173: \n174: **Known issue**: The existing implementation only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):` — if the condition is false, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 but the CLI layer will catch it via `_handle_error`.\n175: \n176: ```python\n177: async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path):\n178:     metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n179: \n180:     # URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n181:     if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n182:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n183:         agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n184:         # Extract base URL from original endpoint\n185:         base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n186:         endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n187: \n188:     # Build headers\n189:     request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n190:     if metadata.session_id:\n191:         request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n192: \n193:     # POST via httpx\n194:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n195:         response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n196:         response.raise_for_status()\n197:         return response.json()\n198: ```\n199: \n200: #### 3.1.4 `_direct_http_invocation()` — Standard K8s invocation\n201: \n202: Direct HTTP POST to the agent endpoint (NodePort Service URL):\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path):\n206:     metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n207: \n208:     request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n209:     if metadata.session_id:\n210:         request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n211: \n212:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n213:         response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n214:         response.raise_for_status()\n215:         return response.json()\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### 3.2 StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: class StatusRuntime:\n222:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n223:     def get_status(\n224:         self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None\n225:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n226:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n227:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n228: ```\n229: \n230: #### 3.2.1 `get_status()` — Main orchestration\n231: \n232: ```python\n233: def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n234:     provider = provider or self.provider\n235:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n236:     metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n237: \n238:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n239:         return {\"status\": \"not_published\"}\n240: \n241:     if provider == \"agentcube\":\n242:         return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n243:     else:\n244:         return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n245: ```\n246: \n247: #### 3.2.2 `_get_cr_k8s_status()` — AgentRuntime CR status\n248: \n249: ```python\n250: def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n251:     namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n252:     cr_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n253: \n254:     provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n255:     cr_object = provider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n256: \n257:     if cr_object is None:\n258:         return {\n259:             \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n260:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n261:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n262:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n263:         }\n264: \n265:     cr_status = cr_object.get(\"status\", {})\n266:     if cr_status:\n267:         return {\n268:             \"status\": cr_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n269:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n270:             \"endpoint\": cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\", metadata.agent_endpoint),\n271:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n272:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n273:             \"version\": metadata.version,\n274:         }\n275:     else:\n276:         return {\n277:             \"status\": \"created_no_status\",\n278:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n279:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n280:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n281:             \"version\": metadata.version,\n282:         }\n283: ```\n284: \n285: #### 3.2.3 `_get_k8s_status()` — Standard K8s deployment status\n286: \n287: Requires `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` to be added (see §3.4):\n288: \n289: ```python\n290: def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n291:     namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n292:     deployment_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"deployment_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n293: \n294:     provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n295:     return provider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### 3.3 CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n299: \n300: #### 3.3.1 `invoke` command\n301: \n302: ```python\n303: @app.command()\n304: def invoke(\n305:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n306:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent.\"),\n307:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n308:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n309:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n310: ) -> None:\n311:     \"\"\"Invoke a deployed agent with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n312: ```\n313: \n314: **Implementation flow:**\n315: 1. Parse `payload` as JSON — on failure, print error in red and `typer.Exit(1)` (before `_handle_error`)\n316: 2. Parse `header_list` — split each on first `:` to produce `Dict[str, str]`; on invalid format, print error and `typer.Exit(1)`\n317: 3. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n318: 4. Call `runtime.invoke(Path(workspace), payload_dict, headers)`\n319: 5. Print response (Rich-formatted JSON if dict, raw text otherwise)\n320: 6. On exception, call `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n321: \n322: #### 3.3.2 `status` command\n323: \n324: ```python\n325: @app.command()\n326: def status(\n327:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n328:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n329:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n330: ) -> None:\n331:     \"\"\"Check the status of a deployed agent.\"\"\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Implementation flow:**\n335: 1. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n336: 2. Call `runtime.get_status(Path(workspace), provider)`\n337: 3. If `status == \"not_published\"`: print guidance to run `publish` first, `typer.Exit(1)`\n338: 4. If `status == \"error\"`: print error details, `typer.Exit(1)`\n339: 5. Render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value\n340: 6. On exception (not `typer.Exit`), call `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n341: \n342: ### 3.4 KubernetesProvider extension\n343: \n344: Add `get_agent_status()` method to `KubernetesProvider`:\n345: \n346: ```python\n347: def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n348:     \"\"\"Get the status of a deployed agent.\n349: \n350:     Args:\n351:         agent_name: Name of the deployment.\n352: \n353:     Returns:\n354:         Dict with status, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas, etc.\n355:     \"\"\"\n356:     try:\n357:         deployment = self._apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n358:             name=agent_name,\n359:             namespace=self.namespace,\n360:         )\n361:         status = deployment.status\n362:         return {\n363:             \"status\": \"running\" if (status.ready_replicas and status.ready_replicas > 0) else \"pending\",\n364:             \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n365:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n366:             \"replicas\": status.replicas,\n367:             \"ready_replicas\": status.ready_replicas,\n368:             \"available_replicas\": status.available_replicas,\n369:             \"updated_replicas\": status.updated_replicas,\n370:         }\n371:     except ApiException as e:\n372:         if e.status == 404:\n373:             return {\n374:                 \"status\": \"not_found\",\n375:                 \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n376:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n377:             }\n378:         raise\n379: ```\n380: \n381: ### 3.5 Sentinel Errors\n382: \n383: ```python\n384: # InvokeRuntime\n385: ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n386: ValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n387: \n388: # StatusRuntime\n389: # Returns dict with status field — no exceptions for logical states\n390: \n391: # CLI layer\n392: typer.Exit(1) — invalid JSON payload\n393: typer.Exit(1) — invalid header format\n394: typer.Exit(1) — not_published status\n395: typer.Exit(1) — error status\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## Data Flow Details\n401: \n402: ### 4.1 invoke() CLI → Runtime → HTTP\n403: \n404: ```\n405: CLI invoke()\n406:   │\n407:   ├── json.loads(payload) ──→ JSONDecodeError → print error, exit 1\n408:   │\n409:   ├── parse headers ──→ invalid format → print error, exit 1\n410:   │\n411:   ├── InvokeRuntime.invoke(workspace, payload_dict, headers)\n412:   │     │\n413:   │     ├── _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n414:   │     │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n415:   │     │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → ValueError if missing\n416:   │     │     └── check metadata.agent_endpoint → ValueError if missing\n417:   │     │\n418:   │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n419:   │           ├── YES → _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n420:   │           │         ├── URL rewrite if k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"\n421:   │           │         ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n422:   │           │         └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n423:   │           │\n424:   │           └── NO → _direct_http_invocation()\n425:   │                     ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n426:   │                     └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n427:   │\n428:   └── Print response (JSON-formatted or raw text)\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ### 4.2 status() CLI → Runtime → K8s API → Rich Table\n432: \n433: ```\n434: CLI status()\n435:   │\n436:   ├── StatusRuntime.get_status(workspace, provider)\n437:   │     │\n438:   │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n439:   │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → return {\"status\": \"not_published\"} if missing\n440:   │     │\n441:   │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n442:   │           ├── YES → _get_cr_k8s_status()\n443:   │           │         ├── AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n444:   │           │         ├── CR not found → {\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\", ...}\n445:   │           │         ├── CR has status → {\"status\": cr_status[\"status\"], \"endpoint\": ..., ...}\n446:   │           │         └── CR exists but no status → {\"status\": \"created_no_status\", ...}\n447:   │           │\n448:   │           └── NO → _get_k8s_status()\n449:   │                     ├── KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n450:   │                     ├── Deployment not found → {\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}\n451:   │                     └── Deployment found → {\"status\": \"running\"/\"pending\", replicas, ...}\n452:   │\n453:   ├── status == \"not_published\"? → print guidance, exit 1\n454:   ├── status == \"error\"? → print error, exit 1\n455:   │\n456:   └── Render Rich Table:\n457:         ┌─────────────────┬──────────────────┐\n458:         │ Field           │ Value            │\n459:         ├─────────────────┼──────────────────┤\n460:         │ Agent Name      │ test-agent       │\n461:         │ Status          │ running          │\n462:         │ Endpoint        │ http://...       │\n463:         │ Version         │ v1.0.0           │\n464:         │ Provider        │ agentcube        │\n465:         │ ...             │ ...              │\n466:         └─────────────────┴──────────────────┘\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### 4.3 Header parsing logic\n470: \n471: ```python\n472: headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n473: if header_list:\n474:     headers = {}\n475:     for h in header_list:\n476:         if \":\" not in h:\n477:             typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{h}'. Expected 'key:value'.\", err=True)\n478:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n479:         key, value = h.split(\":\", 1)\n480:         headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### 4.4 URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n484: \n485: When `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`:\n486: \n487: ```python\n488: namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n489: agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n490: base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n491: endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## Error Handling\n497: \n498: ### 5.1 Error Handling Strategy\n499: \n500: | Error Type | Handling | Exit Code |\n501: |------------|----------|-----------|\n502: | Invalid JSON payload | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n503: | Invalid header format | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n504: | Agent not published (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n505: | Agent endpoint missing (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n506: | HTTP error during invoke | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n507: | K8s client init failure (status) | `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)` | 1 |\n508: | not_published status | Print guidance, exit immediately | 1 |\n509: | error status | Print error details, exit immediately | 1 |\n510: | CR not found in K8s (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n511: | Deployment not found (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n512: \n513: ### 5.2 CLI Error Handler (existing, reused)\n514: \n515: ```python\n516: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n517:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n518:     if verbose:\n519:         console.print_exception()\n520:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n521: ```\n522: \n523: ### 5.3 Verbose vs Global Verbose\n524: \n525: The subcommand's local `--verbose` flag is passed to `_handle_error`, ensuring traceback is printed even if global `-v` was not passed on the root callback.\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Testing Strategy\n530: \n531: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n532: \n533: #### InvokeRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`)\n534: \n535: | Test Name | Description |\n536: |-----------|-------------|\n537: | `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeAgentCube` | Valid workspace, agentcube provider → invokes successfully |\n538: | `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeK8s` | Valid workspace, k8s provider → direct HTTP invocation |\n539: | `TestInvokeRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id in metadata → `ValueError` |\n540: | `TestInvokeRuntime_MissingEndpoint` | No agent_endpoint in metadata → `ValueError` |\n541: | `TestInvokeRuntime_URLRewriting` | k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\" → endpoint rewritten |\n542: | `TestInvokeRuntime_SessionHeader` | session_id in metadata → X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added |\n543: | `TestInvokeRuntime_CustomHeaders` | Custom headers passed through |\n544: | `TestInvokeRuntime_HTTPError` | Non-2xx response → exception raised |\n545: | `TestInvokeRuntime_UnboundLocalError` | Known bug: non-http endpoint → caught by CLI _handle_error |\n546: \n547: #### StatusRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`)\n548: \n549: | Test Name | Description |\n550: |-----------|-------------|\n551: | `TestStatusRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id → `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}` |\n552: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeExists` | CR exists with status → correct status dict |\n553: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeNoStatus` | CR exists but no status field → `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}` |\n554: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRNotFound` | CR not found → `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` |\n555: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentRunning` | K8s deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n556: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentPending` | K8s deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n557: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentNotFound` | K8s deployment 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n558: | `TestStatusRuntime_ProviderSelection` | Provider parameter routes to correct method |\n559: \n560: #### CLI invoke Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py`)\n561: \n562: | Test Name | Description |\n563: |-----------|-------------|\n564: | `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `invoke --provider agentcube` → success output, exit 0 |\n565: | `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessK8s` | `invoke --provider k8s` → success output, exit 0 |\n566: | `TestInvokeCommand_DefaultPayload` | `invoke` (no --payload) → uses `\"{}\"` |\n567: | `TestInvokeCommand_CustomPayload` | `invoke --payload '{\"key\":\"value\"}'` → correct JSON parsed |\n568: | `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidPayload` | `invoke --payload '{bad}'` → error, exit 1 |\n569: | `TestInvokeCommand_SingleHeader` | `invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` → parsed |\n570: | `TestInvokeCommand_MultipleHeaders` | `invoke --header \"A:1\" --header \"B:2\"` → merged |\n571: | `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidHeader` | `invoke --header \"BadHeader\"` → error, exit 1 |\n572: | `TestInvokeCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n573: | `TestInvokeCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n574: | `TestInvokeCommand_HelpOutput` | `invoke --help` → shows all options |\n575: \n576: #### CLI status Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_status_command.py`)\n577: \n578: | Test Name | Description |\n579: |-----------|-------------|\n580: | `TestStatusCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `status --provider agentcube` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n581: | `TestStatusCommand_SuccessK8s` | `status --provider k8s` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n582: | `TestStatusCommand_NotPublished` | No agent_id → guidance message, exit 1 |\n583: | `TestStatusCommand_ErrorStatus` | status == \"error\" → error message, exit 1 |\n584: | `TestStatusCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n585: | `TestStatusCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n586: | `TestStatusCommand_HelpOutput` | `status --help` → shows all options |\n587: \n588: #### KubernetesProvider Tests (extension) (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n589: \n590: | Test Name | Description |\n591: |-----------|-------------|\n592: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusRunning` | Deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n593: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusPending` | Deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n594: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusNotFound` | 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n595: \n596: ### 6.2 Test Helpers\n597: \n598: ```python\n599: @pytest.fixture\n600: def workspace_with_published_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n601:     ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n602:     ws.mkdir()\n603:     (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n604:     (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n605:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\n\"\n606:         \"language: python\\n\"\n607:         \"entrypoint: python main.py\\n\"\n608:         \"port: 8080\\n\"\n609:         \"build_mode: local\\n\"\n610:         \"agent_id: test-agent-123\\n\"\n611:         \"agent_endpoint: http://router.example.com/v1/agents/test-agent\\n\"\n612:         \"k8s_deployment:\\n\"\n613:         \"  type: AgentRuntime\\n\"\n614:         \"  namespace: default\\n\"\n615:         \"  cr_name: test-agent\\n\"\n616:     )\n617:     return ws\n618: \n619: @pytest.fixture\n620: def mock_httpx_client(mocker):\n621:     mock_response = MagicMock()\n622:     mock_response.json.return_value = {\"output\": \"hello world\"}\n623:     mock_response.raise_for_status.return_value = None\n624: \n625:     mock_client = MagicMock()\n626:     mock_client.__aenter__ = AsyncMock(return_value=mock_client)\n627:     mock_client.__aexit__ = AsyncMock(return_value=None)\n628:     mock_client.post.return_value = mock_response\n629: \n630:     mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\", return_value=mock_client)\n631:     return mock_client\n632: ```\n633: \n634: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n635: \n636: - **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n637: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n638: - **httpx.AsyncClient:** Mock `post()`, `__aenter__`, `__aexit__`\n639: - **AgentCubeProvider:** Mock `get_agent_runtime()`\n640: - **KubernetesProvider:** Mock `get_agent_status()`\n641: - **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n642: \n643: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n644: \n645: 1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n646: 2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n647: 3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n648: 4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n649: 5. All InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime public methods have unit tests\n650: 6. Error paths tested (invalid payload, invalid header, not published, HTTP errors)\n651: 7. Both provider flows tested (agentcube and k8s) for invoke and status\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Implementation Notes\n656: \n657: 1. **async/await in CLI**: `InvokeRuntime` uses `async` methods internally but the CLI command runs them synchronously via `asyncio.run()`. This avoids making the Typer command async.\n658: \n659: 2. **httpx vs requests**: The invoke command uses `httpx` (already a dependency) for async HTTP. The Python SDK uses `requests`, but the CLI layer should use `httpx` for consistency with the async pattern in `InvokeRuntime`.\n660: \n661: 3. **URL rewriting edge case**: If the original endpoint doesn't contain `/v1/`, the base URL extraction falls back to the full endpoint (stripped of trailing slashes). This handles both `http://router/v1/...` and `http://localhost:30080` formats.\n662: \n663: 4. **Session header spelling**: The header is `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (note: not `X-AgentCube-Session-Id`). This matches the SDK's `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase, HTTP headers are case-insensitive).\n664: \n665: 5. **Provider default**: Both commands default to `provider=\"agentcube\"`, consistent with the `publish` command.\n666: \n667: 6. **KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()**: This method does not exist yet and must be added. It queries `read_namespaced_deployment_status()` and returns a dict with status fields. 404 is handled gracefully (returns `not_found` status dict, not an exception).\n668: \n669: 7. **Known UnboundLocalError**: `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` has a known bug where `response` is only assigned inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`. If the endpoint doesn't start with `http`, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 — the CLI layer catches it via `_handle_error` and the user sees a friendly error message.\n670: \n671: 8. **Rich Table rendering**: The status command renders a table with all key-value pairs from the status dict. The table should include at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider.\n672: \n673: 9. **No new dependencies**: All required libraries (httpx, rich, typer, pydantic, pyyaml, kubernetes) are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n674: \n675: 10. **runtime/__init__.py update**: After creating `invoke_runtime.py` and `status_runtime.py`, update `runtime/__init__.py` to export `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime`.\n676: \n677: 11. **agentcube/__init__.py update**: After creating the runtime classes, update the top-level `__init__.py` to include `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` in exports (note: `StatusRuntime` was explicitly not exported before — this AR adds it).\n\n(End of file - total 677 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\n\nBoth commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n│   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\n│   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775857489629,"end":1775857489638}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857491008,"sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","part":{"id":"prt_d795ad76a001ugaC5uj4C6jbTd","messageID":"msg_d795ac4cf001rXStxP6u3Htbfl","sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_68a6c32af32a4b6b9a04d96f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that sends an HTTP request to a deployed agent endpoint.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Command signature\n17: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n18: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke --help`\n19: - **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace, input/prompt, and verbose\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Invoke with endpoint from metadata\n22: - **GIVEN** the workspace has been published and `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `agent_endpoint`\n23: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke -f <workspace> --prompt \"hello\"`\n24: - **THEN** the system SHALL send an HTTP POST request to the endpoint and display the response\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Invoke without published endpoint\n27: - **GIVEN** the workspace has not been published or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n28: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke`\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the agent has not been published\n30: \n31: ### Requirement: `status` command\n32: \n33: The system SHALL provide a `status` subcommand that queries the deployment status of an agent.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Command signature\n36: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n37: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status --help`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace and verbose\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Status from AgentRuntime CR\n41: - **GIVEN** the agent was published with `provider=agentcube`\n42: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status -f <workspace>`\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the AgentRuntime CR status and display it\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Status from K8s Deployment\n46: - **GIVEN** the agent was published with `provider=k8s`\n47: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status -f <workspace>`\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the Deployment status and display it\n49: \n50: ## File changes\n51: \n52: | Action | File | Description |\n53: |--------|------|-------------|\n54: | Modify | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `invoke` and `status` Typer commands |\n55: | Add | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime class |\n56: | Modify | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Enhance StatusRuntime class |\n57: | Add | `tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py` | CLI invoke command tests |\n58: | Add | `tests/cli/test_status_command.py` | CLI status command tests |\n59: | Add | `tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime unit tests |\n60: | Add | `tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py` | StatusRuntime unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `invoke` command\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that sends an HTTP request to a deployed agent endpoint.\n\n#### Scenario: Command signature\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke --help`\n- **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace, input/prompt, and verbose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857490995,"end":1775857491006}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857492302,"sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","part":{"id":"prt_d795adcc6001aSj2VQMsulFOhf","messageID":"msg_d795ac4cf001rXStxP6u3Htbfl","sessionID":"ses_286a547f1ffeZpobFdTX1gJ7fx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_37f1ec61dc3449f392ab3f89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-023/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-023/design.md`, `changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** AR-022 (publish command) — requires published agent endpoint\n9: \n10: ## T1. 实现 InvokeRuntime 类\n11: \n12: - [ ] 1.1 创建 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n13: - [ ] 1.2 定义 `InvokeRuntime` 类：`__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n14: - [ ] 1.3 实现 `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n15:   - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n16:   - 校验 `agent_endpoint` 存在 → 否则 `ValueError`\n17:   - 发送 HTTP POST 请求到 endpoint\n18:   - 返回响应结果\n19: - [ ] 1.4 创建对应测试文件\n20: \n21: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py -v` 全部通过\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## T2. 增强 StatusRuntime 类\n26: \n27: - [ ] 2.1 修改 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n28: - [ ] 2.2 实现 `status(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n29:   - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n30:   - 根据 `k8s_deployment.type` 路由到正确的状态查询\n31:   - 返回状态信息\n32: - [ ] 2.3 实现/增强 `_get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n33: - [ ] 2.4 创建对应测试文件\n34: \n35: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py -v` 全部通过\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## T3. 实现 CLI invoke 命令入口\n40: \n41: - [ ] 3.1 在 `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` 中添加 `invoke` 命令\n42: - [ ] 3.2 选项：`workspace`, `prompt`, `verbose`\n43: - [ ] 3.3 命令体：调用 `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`，Rich 格式输出响应\n44: - [ ] 3.4 创建对应测试文件\n45: \n46: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py -v` 全部通过\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## T4. 实现 CLI status 命令入口\n51: \n52: - [ ] 4.1 在 `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` 中添加 `status` 命令\n53: - [ ] 4.2 选项：`workspace`, `verbose`\n54: - [ ] 4.3 命令体：调用 `StatusRuntime.status()`，Rich Table 格式输出状态\n55: - [ ] 4.4 创建对应测试文件\n56: \n57: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_status_command.py -v` 全部通过\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## T5. 代码质量门禁与最终验证\n62: \n63: - [ ] 5.1 运行 `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认无 lint 错误\n64: - [ ] 5.2 运行 `ruff format --check cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认格式合规\n65: - [ ] 5.3 运行 `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认无类型错误\n66: - [ ] 5.4 运行 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube` 确认覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n67: - [ ] 5.5 运行 `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` 确认帮助输出\n68: - [ ] 5.6 运行 `kubectl-agentcube status --help` 确认帮助输出\n69: \n70: **Verification:** 以上全部通过；exit code 均为 0\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## Task Dependencies\n75: \n76: ```\n77: T1 (InvokeRuntime) ───────────────────────────────┐\n78:                                                    │\n79: T2 (StatusRuntime) ────────────────────────────────┤\n80:                                                    │\n81: T3 (CLI invoke 命令) ←── T1 ───────────────────────┤\n82:                                                    │\n83: T4 (CLI status 命令) ←── T2 ───────────────────────┤\n84:                                                    │\n85: T5 (质量门禁) ←── T3, T4 ──────────────────────────┘\n86: ```\n87: \n88: **Parallel execution:**\n89: - T1 和 T2 可并行开发\n90: - T3 需 T1 完成后开始\n91: - T4 需 T2 完成后开始\n92: - T3 和 T4 可并行开发\n93: - T5 需所有前置任务完成\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Acceptance Criteria\n98: \n99: | # | Criterion | Command |\n100: |---|-----------|---------|\n101: | AC1 | invoke 命令接受 workspace 和 prompt 选项 | `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` |\n102: | AC2 | status 命令接受 workspace 选项 | `kubectl-agentcube status --help` |\n103: | AC3 | 未发布的 agent invoke 报错 | 无 `agent_endpoint` → `ValueError` |\n104: | AC4 | invoke 发送 HTTP 请求并显示响应 | Rich 格式输出 |\n105: | AC5 | status 查询并显示部署状态 | Rich Table 格式 |\n106: | AC6 | 覆盖率 ≥ 80% | `pytest --cov=agentcube` |\n107: | AC7 | ruff lint 无错误 | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n108: | AC8 | mypy 类型检查无错误 | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-023/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-023/design.md`, `changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** AR-022 (publish command) — requires published agent endpoint\n\n## T1. 实现 InvokeRuntime 类\n\n- [ ] 1.1 创建 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n- [ ] 1.2 定义 `InvokeRuntime` 类：`__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n- [ ] 1.3 实现 `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n  - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - 校验 `agent_endpoint` 存在 → 否则 `ValueError`\n  - 发送 HTTP POST 请求到 endpoint\n  - 返回响应结果\n- [ ] 1.4 创建对应测试文件\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775857492292,"end":1775857492300}}}}
